cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper discusses the convergence and performance of a recently proposed optimizer, AdaBound, in the context of training neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the theoretical properties of AdaBound, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
